  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Justice and Development for All is committed to support the government in improving the quality of education of primary schools at Nguruka Ward which has  more than 5500+ school pupils. The primary schools  face shortage of important teaching materials , text books, and teaching aids are not sufficient to meet the need. Currently, the book ration is 1:4 pupils, forcing some of pupils to be demoralized as they don&apos;t perform exercise nor get time to perform assignment given by teachers .</narrative>
  </description>
